!!!
%html
  %head
    %meta{:content => "text/html; charset=UTF-8", "http-equiv" => "Content-Type"}/
    %meta{:charset => "ISO-8859-1"}/
    %title CosmoFarmer Gallery
    %link{:href => "styles.css", :rel => "stylesheet"}/
    /[if lt IE 9]
      %script{:src => "../html5shiv.js"}
    :css
      figure img {
        border: 1px solid #666;
        background-color: #FFF;
        padding: 4px;
        box-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, .5);
      }

      figcaption {
        font: 1.1em/normal Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 10px 0 0 0;
      }

      figure {
        display: inline-block;
        vertical-align: top;
        width: 210px;
        margin: 0 10px 10px 10px;
      }


  %body
    .content
      %h1 CosmoFarmer.com’s Indoor Grass Photo Gallery
      %p.intro
        A selection of indoor sod options: reviewed and tested by
        %strong CosmoFarmer.com
        in our state-of-the-art “Apartment Laboratory” on 5th Avenue.
      .gallery
        %figure
          %img{:alt => "Carpet Grass", :height => "200", :src => "../images/carpet.jpg", :width => "200"}/
          %figcaption
            Figure 1: Even the carpet-like
            %em Carpetorium Pratensis
            requires mowing.
        %figure
          %img{:alt => "Bentgrass", :height => "200", :src => "../images/grass.jpg", :width => "200"}/
          %figcaption Figure 2: Creeping Bentgrass is best suited for outdoor use and should be avoided by the indoor farmer.
        %figure
          %img{:alt => "Bluegrass", :height => "200", :src => "../images/bluegrass.jpg", :width => "200"}/
          %figcaption Figure 3: This indoor-hybrid of Kentucky Bluegrass has fallen out of fashion.
        %figure
          %img{:alt => "Leaves", :height => "200", :src => "../images/leaves.jpg", :width => "200"}/
          %figcaption
            Figure 4:
            %em Tinea Pedis Poaceae
            threatens discomfort to bare feet.
        %figure
          %img{:alt => "Pattern Grass", :height => "200", :src => "../images/pattern.jpg", :width => "200"}/
          %figcaption Figure 5: The difficult to maintain pattern of this indoor lawn is a sight to behold.
        %figure
          %img{:alt => "Dandelion", :height => "200", :src => "../images/dandelion.jpg", :width => "200"}/
          %figcaption Figure 6: The dandelion: scourge of the apartment farmer.
      %p.copyright Copyright 2012, CosmoFarmer.com
